	<pb facs="liv_002007_0002" n="0002"/>
         
	<pb facs="liv_002007_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/><opener><dateline rend="no-indent"><space extent="2" unit="words"/><placeName><country><choice><orig>Mosambique</orig><reg>Mozambique</reg></choice></country></placeName> <date when="1864-03-07">7<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> March
<lb/><space extent="8" unit="words"/>1864</date></dateline></opener>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">I hereby certify that <persName>John
<lb/>Pennell</persName> served in the <orgName><placeName><geogName type="river">Zambesi</geogName></placeName>
<lb/>Expedition</orgName> from <date from="1861-03-11" to="1864-02-15">11<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> March 1861
<lb/>to 15<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> February 1864</date> and              
<lb/>during the whole of that time
<lb/>his conduct has given me
<lb/>the greatest satisfaction - He
<lb/>is thoroughly well behaved,
<lb/>very attentive to his duty
<lb/>and always respectful to
<lb/>his superiors - He seems
<lb/>good tempered - very obliging - -
<lb/>He knows his duty &amp;
<lb/>has certainly performed
<lb/>it well - I can recommend
<lb/><choice><sic>-</sic><corr></corr></choice>him strongly to his superiors
<lb/>as a thoroughly trustworthy
<lb/>honest man</p>              
<lb/><closer><space extent="2" unit="words"/><signed><persName>David Livingstone</persName></signed></closer> 
            </div>
        </body>
